==Introduction==

===Abstract===

This document augments Taproot ([[bip-0341.mediawiki|BIP 341]]) key-path spending to require disclosure of the internal public key via the annex, and bans key-path spending when the internal key matches a known "Nothing Up My Sleeve" (NUMS) point. Outputs constructed without a taproot tweak (bare-key outputs) can no longer be spent via key-path after activation.

This BIP is a companion to [[bip-0369.mediawiki|BIP 369]] (OP_CHECKSPHINCSVERIFY) and may be activated simultaneously. Together, they provide a complete post-quantum defense: BIP 369 enables SPHINCS+ signature verification in Tapscript, while this BIP hardens key-path spending against quantum ECDLP attacks.

